{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Serializing with an XML Declaration (C#)\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nms.assetid: c237fa4a-a042-40fd-886f-17b54c66bb75\n---\n# Serializing with an XML Declaration (C#)\nThis topic describes how to control whether serialization generates an XML declaration.  \n  \n## XML Declaration Generation  \n Serializing to a <xref:System.IO.File> or a <xref:System.IO.TextWriter> using the <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XElement.Save%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method or the <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XDocument.Save%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method generates an XML declaration. When you serialize to an <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>, the writer settings (specified in an <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriterSettings> object) determine whether an XML declaration is generated or not.  \n  \n If you are serializing to a string using the `ToString` method, the resulting XML will not include an XML declaration.  \n  \n### Serializing with an XML Declaration  \n The following example creates an <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XElement>, saves the document to a file, and then prints the file to the console:  \n  \n```csharp  \nXElement root = new XElement(\"Root\",  \n    new XElement(\"Child\", \"child content\")  \n);  \nroot.Save(\"Root.xml\");  \nstring str = File.ReadAllText(\"Root.xml\");  \nConsole.WriteLine(str);  \n```  \n  \n This example produces the following output:  \n  \n```xml  \n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>  \n<Root>  \n  <Child>child content</Child>  \n</Root>  \n```  \n  \n### Serializing without an XML Declaration  \n The following example shows how to save an <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XElement> to an <xref:System.Xml.XmlWriter>.  \n  \n```csharp  \nStringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();  \nXmlWriterSettings xws = new XmlWriterSettings();  \nxws.OmitXmlDeclaration = true;  \n  \nusing (XmlWriter xw = XmlWriter.Create(sb, xws)) {  \n    XElement root = new XElement(\"Root\",  \n        new XElement(\"Child\", \"child content\")  \n    );  \n    root.Save(xw);  \n}  \nConsole.WriteLine(sb.ToString());  \n```  \n  \n This example produces the following output:  \n  \n```xml  \n<Root><Child>child content</Child></Root>  \n```  \n  \n## See also\n\n- [Serializing XML Trees (C#)](../../../../csharp/programming-guide/concepts/linq/serializing-xml-trees.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,122],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Serializing with an XML Declaration (C#)\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nms.assetid: c237fa4a-a042-40fd-886f-17b54c66bb75","nodes":[{"content":"Serializing with an XML Declaration (C#)","nodes":[{"pos":[0,40],"content":"Serializing with an XML Declaration (C#)","nodes":[{"content":"Serializing with an XML Declaration (C#)","pos":[0,40]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[129,169],"content":"Serializing with an XML Declaration (C#)","linkify":"Serializing with an XML Declaration (C#)","nodes":[{"content":"Serializing with an XML Declaration (C#)","pos":[0,40]}]},{"content":"This topic describes how to control whether serialization generates an XML declaration.","pos":[170,257]},{"pos":[266,292],"content":"XML Declaration Generation","linkify":"XML Declaration Generation","nodes":[{"content":"XML Declaration Generation","pos":[0,26]}]},{"content":"Serializing to a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.IO.File&gt;</ph> or a <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.IO.TextWriter&gt;</ph> using the <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Xml.Linq.XElement.Save%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> method or the <ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;xref:System.Xml.Linq.XDocument.Save%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> method generates an XML declaration.","pos":[296,567],"source":"Serializing to a <xref:System.IO.File> or a <xref:System.IO.TextWriter> using the <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XElement.Save%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method or the <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XDocument.Save%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method generates an XML declaration."},{"content":"When you serialize to an <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Xml.Xm